</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ragge, DR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology" pageId="16" pageNumber="33" pagination="269 - 333" title="The Acrometopae of the Ethiopian Region: a revision, with notes on the sexual dimorphism shown by the group (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2245318page/386/mode/1up" volume="8" year="1960">Ragge (1960)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Horatosphaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Horatosphaga leggei" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leggei">Horatosphaga leggei</taxonomicName>
is the most common species of the genus from East Africa to the Democratic Republic of Congo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
